<recipe>
<title>
Slow Cooker Pork Barbacoa
</title>
<details>

</details>
<ingredients>
4-5 lb . pork butt or shoulder roast
1 (10 oz.) can red enchilada sauce
2 (4 oz.) cans green chiles
1 (12 oz.) can Coca Cola
1/2 c . brown sugar
2 cloves garlic
1 tsp . salt
1/2 tsp . pepper
</ingredients>
<instructions>
Blend together enchilada sauce, green chiles, Coke, brown sugar, garlic, salt, and pepper until smooth.
Place roast in crockpot fat side down.
Pour sauce over meat.
Cover and cook on low for 8-10 hours.
Shred pork, and continue to cook for 30 minutes-1 hour.
</instructions>
</recipe>
